a H100 GPUs to run, making it impractical for most consumer hardware.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hosted Access&lt;/strong&gt;: Due to its size, many users rely on Sand AI&amp;rsquo;s platform to test Magi-1.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;-the-censorship-conundrum&#34;&gt;🛑 The Censorship Conundrum&lt;a href=&#34;#-the-censorship-conundrum&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;      stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M15 7h3a5 5 0 0 1 5 5 5 5 0 0 1-5 5h-3m-6 0H6a5 5 0 0 1-5-5 5 5 0 0 1 5-5h3&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;      &lt;line x1=&#34;8&#34; y1=&#34;12&#34; x2=&#34;16&#34; y2=&#34;12&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&#xA;   &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;While Magi-1 showcases impressive capabilities, it comes with a catch:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
